Meet <b>Jake</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Jake has been living happily at <a href='/home/?user=bulldawg_fan1'>95283-C Hunter Road</a>, in Lakeview, ever since June 4th, 2008. <br><br>Jake loves Lakeview's cool breeze that comes right off the lake. He's a big water person, so he likes to take advantage of all of the water sports available on the lake.<br><br>In the short time he's lived here, Jake has been hard at work. In fact, he's already managed to climb to the top of the chart of the surfing circuit, out at Okalani Island with Kai's Surfari. <br><br>Jake's also managed to master Sink Three and Home Run Derby. Seems like his eye-hand coordination is up to par. So is his foot-eye coordination: He has a trophy for the Peabody Park half-pipe, too.<br><br>Basketball and Baseball are both interests of Jake's, so it's no wonder he's excelled at both on his own. And, when he's not playing baseball or basketball, you can probably find Jake at the amusement park. Everybody needs to relax once in a while, right?<br><br>If you happen to see Jake, make sure you shake his hand and thank him for being such an outstanding citizen!</div>
